cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for large-scale recognition tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions image and speech recognition tasks, which are common in the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new technique for approximating dot products, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of their approach, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
